---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import SubwayMap from '../components/SubwayMap.svg?raw';

const stations = await getCollection('curriculum');
const essays = await getCollection('essays');

const featuredEssay = essays.find((e) => e.id === 'a-little-help-for-my-friends') ?? essays[0];
---

<Base
  title="Vol. I, No. I"
  description="A Naturalist's Record of an Investigation from First Principles to the Frontier of Quantum Gravity. Vol. I, No. I."
>
  <a href="#main" class="skip">Skip to contents</a>

  <div class="page">

    <header class="masthead">
      <div class="masthead-corners">
        <span>No. I</span>
        <span>Bend &middot; Oregon</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="masthead-title">
        <span class="masthead-title-main">The Donkey</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-conn">on the</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-main">Edge</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="masthead-strap">
        A Naturalist's Record of an Investigation from First Principles<br />
        to the Frontier of Quantum Gravity.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead-line">
        <span class="masthead-line-rule"></span>
        <span class="masthead-meta">
          <span>Vol. I</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>No. I</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>May MMXXVI</span>
        </span>
        <span class="masthead-line-rule"></span>
      </div>
      <nav class="masthead-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/paper">The Paper</a>
        <span class="ms-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/curriculum">The Curriculum</a>
        <span class="ms-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/field-notes">Field Notes</a>
        <span class="ms-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/method">The Method</a>
        <span class="ms-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/lab">The Lab</a>
        <span class="ms-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="main">

      <!-- ━━ LEAD ━━ -->
      <section class="lead" aria-label="Lead Story">
        <p class="lead-kicker">Lead Story &middot; Vol. I, No. I &middot; The Frontier</p>
        <h2 class="lead-headline">
          A Non-Physicist and an A.I. Walked to the Frontier of <em>Quantum Gravity.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="lead-deck">
          Eighteen days. Thirty-eight reference documents. One paper, headed for the arXiv. The full record, begun in Bend, Oregon and ended at the edge of the field, is presented herein.
        </p>
        <div class="lead-body">
          <figure class="lead-plate">
            <div class="plate">
              <div class="plate-inner">
                <img src="/images/donkeyedge.png" alt="A donkey upon the edge of a cliff, looking out over the investigation." width="800" height="600" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <figcaption class="plate-caption">
              <span class="fig">Fig. I.</span> Donkey upon the Edge of the Investigation. Drawn from life, April MMXXVI.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <p><span class="lead-dropcap">O</span>n the twenty-third of April in the year MMXXVI, a man in Bend, Oregon asked an artificial intelligence where to start learning quantum mechanics. The conversation proceeded, in a single unbroken thread, from <em>F&nbsp;=&nbsp;ma</em> to the open problems of quantum gravity. By the eleventh of May, a paper had been written: a proof of two theorems, a verified empirical scaling law, and one integer-valued exponent gap that nobody has yet explained.</p>
          <p>This site is the record. It is presented as a Victorian scientific journal because the work it documents, a generalist setting out from first principles in pursuit of a question at the edge of human knowledge, belongs to that tradition. The curriculum is presented as a railway chart. The paper is presented as a folio. The field notes are presented as a notebook, open. Everything is here; the wrong turns are kept on the page along with the right ones, because the texture of doing the work is itself part of the record.</p>
          <p>What sits at the end of the walk is small and specific. Two observers of the same quantum object, looking through a noisy and irreversible code, disagree about what they see by an amount that depends on the <em>structure</em> of the object. The dependence has a clean closed form for two extremal cases and an integer-valued gap between them. The integer is exactly one. Nobody yet knows why.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lead-cta">
          <a class="btn-primary" href="/paper">Read the Paper</a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="/field-notes/a-little-help-for-my-friends">Start with the Symphony</a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="/curriculum">Study the Map</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="band-rule" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="band-rule-line"></span>
        <span class="band-rule-mark">&#10086;</span>
        <span class="band-rule-line"></span>
      </div>

      <!-- ━━ BELOW THE FOLD : I. THE PAPER (banner) ━━ -->
      <section class="below-fold-head" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="bf-rule"></span>
        <span class="bf-label">Below the Fold &middot; The Three Articles</span>
        <span class="bf-rule"></span>
      </section>

      <article class="banner banner-paper" aria-label="The Paper">
        <header class="banner-head">
          <span class="banner-num">I.</span>
          <p class="banner-eyebrow">The Paper &middot; Article &sect; I</p>
        </header>
        <div class="banner-body">
          <div class="banner-text">
            <h3 class="banner-headline">Five Results. Three Theorems. One Integer Gap.</h3>
            <p class="banner-deck"><em>Complexity-Sensitive Complementarity in Non-Isometric Holographic Codes.</em></p>
            <p class="banner-lede">Two observers look at the same quantum object through the same noisy lens, and disagree. The paper makes the disagreement precise; it has structure, the structure is computable, and the structure depends in a specific way on the complexity of what is being observed. A simple object yields a slow drop in disagreement. A complicated object, a fast one. The gap between the two scalings is <em>exactly one</em>. Nobody yet knows why.</p>
            <div class="banner-cta">
              <a class="btn-primary" href="/paper">Read the Paper</a>
              <a class="btn-secondary" href="/paper/paper1.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF (668 kB)</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="banner-side">
            <ul class="banner-stats">
              <li><span class="stat-n">5</span> <span class="stat-l">Results</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">3</span> <span class="stat-l">Theorems</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">38</span> <span class="stat-l">References</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">1</span> <span class="stat-l">Integer Gap</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="banner-caption">
              <span class="banner-caption-eyebrow">Submitted</span>
              May XI &middot; MMXXVI, headed for arXiv.
            </p>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- ━━ II. THE CURRICULUM + III. FIELD NOTES (two-up) ━━ -->
      <section class="duo" aria-label="Curriculum and Field Notes">

        <article class="duo-card duo-curriculum">
          <header class="duo-head">
            <span class="duo-num">II.</span>
            <p class="duo-eyebrow">The Curriculum &middot; Article &sect; II</p>
          </header>
          <h3 class="duo-headline">Physics 101 to Quantum Gravity, Mapped.</h3>
          <p class="duo-deck">The full path of study, drawn as a Victorian railway chart. Thirty-eight stations on six lines, from Newtonian mechanics to the speculative frontier. All routes terminate at Paper&nbsp;I.</p>
          <figure class="duo-map">
            <div class="duo-map-frame" aria-hidden="true">
              <Fragment set:html={SubwayMap} />
            </div>
            <figcaption>Pl. II &middot; A Chart of the Curriculum &middot; Click stations to read</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <a class="duo-cta" href="/curriculum">Study the Map &rsaquo;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="duo-card duo-field-notes">
          <header class="duo-head">
            <span class="duo-num">III.</span>
            <p class="duo-eyebrow">Field Notes &middot; Article &sect; III</p>
          </header>
          <h3 class="duo-headline">The Notebook, Open. Eighteen Days, Visible.</h3>
          <p class="duo-deck">Phase memos written during the work, essays written about it, and one symphony of an analogy that started the whole thing. The plain-English record, with the wrong turns kept on the page.</p>
          <blockquote class="duo-quote">
            <p>&ldquo;It is not that the universe has one answer for how much two observers can disagree. It has a <em>hierarchy</em> of answers, indexed by how structured the thing they are looking at is. And we can actually compute the hierarchy.&rdquo;</p>
            <cite>From <a href="/field-notes/a-little-help-for-my-friends">A Little Help for My Friends</a></cite>
          </blockquote>
          <a class="duo-cta" href="/field-notes">Open the Notebook &rsaquo;</a>
        </article>

      </section>

      <!-- ━━ FROM THE WIRE ━━ -->
      <aside class="dispatches" aria-labelledby="dispatches-head">
        <div class="dispatches-frame">
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-left">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Latest</span>
          </span>
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-right">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Dispatches</span>
          </span>
          <h3 class="dispatches-head" id="dispatches-head">From the Wire</h3>
          <div class="dispatches-rule" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-mark">&#10086;</span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="dispatches-grid">
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; XI</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Paper&nbsp;I complete.</strong> Five results, three theorems, headed for arXiv pending number assignment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; X</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Phase 8 begun.</strong> The continuation, Paper&nbsp;II, has a published roadmap. <a href="/lab/roadmap">See the plan.</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; IV &middot; XXIII</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Investigation begins.</strong> A man in Bend, Oregon asks Claude where to start with quantum mechanics. The walk to the frontier opens.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="dispatches-foot">
            <span class="pulse" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>The research continues. Updated as it happens.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- ━━ THE METHOD + THE LAB (compact secondaries) ━━ -->
      <section class="secondaries" aria-label="Method and Lab">
        <a href="/method" class="secondary">
          <div class="secondary-num">IV.</div>
          <div class="secondary-body">
            <p class="secondary-eyebrow">The Method</p>
            <h3 class="secondary-headline">On the Doing of This Sort of Work.</h3>
            <p class="secondary-deck">The thesis, the protocol, the failure modes, the calibration log. A guide for other generalists.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="secondary-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/lab" class="secondary">
          <div class="secondary-num">V.</div>
          <div class="secondary-body">
            <p class="secondary-eyebrow">The Laboratory</p>
            <h3 class="secondary-headline">What Is Happening, Now.</h3>
            <p class="secondary-deck">Paper&nbsp;II in progress. Phase memos, code, data, predictions on the record.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="secondary-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
        </a>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</Base>
